sm\nrisk-of-rupture groups (p=0.75), locations (p=0.72), or sizes (p=0.15). Data,\ncode and model weights are released under permissive licenses. We demonstrate\nthat weak labels and anatomical knowledge can alleviate the necessity for\nprohibitively expensive voxel-wise annotations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Mar 2021 16:31:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Apr 2021 13:03:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 28 Sep 2021 15:39:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 5 Oct 2021 09:29:49 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 3 Dec 2021 10:12:50 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 23 Aug 2022 15:29:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-24"}
